
<RelativeLayout xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    xmlns:tools="http://schemas.android.com/tools"
    android:id="@+id/container"
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="match_parent"
    tools:context="com.example.rr.Brhombus"
    tools:ignore="MergeRootFrame" >

    <ScrollView
        android:id="@+id/scrollv"
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"

        >

        <LinearLayout
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:orientation="vertical" >

            <ImageView
                android:id="@+id/imageView1"
                android:layout_width="250dp"
                android:layout_height="250dp"
                android:layout_marginTop="23dp"
                android:layout_gravity="center"
                android:src="@drawable/rhombuss" />

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/textView6"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_alignParentLeft="true"
                android:layout_centerVertical="true"
                android:fontFamily="monospace"
                android:layout_marginLeft="10dp"
                android:textSize="20sp"
                android:text="Definition:"/>
            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/textView7"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_alignParentLeft="true"
                android:layout_centerVertical="true"
                android:layout_marginLeft="10dp"
                android:textSize="18sp"
                android:text="A quadrilateral with all four sides
equal in length.

Rhombus is actually just a special type of parallelogram. Recall that in a parallelogram each pair of opposite sides are equal in length.   With a rhombus, all four sides are the same length.It therefore has all the properties of a parallelogram.

Its a bit like a square that can 'lean over' and the interior angles need not be 90°. Sometimes called a 'diamond' or 'lozenge' shape.
\n\n
"/>


            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/textView3"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_alignParentLeft="true"
                android:layout_centerVertical="true"
                android:fontFamily="monospace"
                android:layout_marginLeft="10dp"
                android:textSize="20sp"
                android:text="Properties of a Rhombus:"/>
            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/textView2"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_alignParentLeft="true"
                android:layout_centerVertical="true"
                android:layout_marginLeft="10dp"
                android:textSize="18sp"
                android:text="\nBase\n\nAny side can be considered a base. \n
Altitude\n\nThe altitude of a rhombus is the perpendicular distance from the base to the opposite side (which may have to be extended). In the figure above, the altitude corresponding to the base CD is shown.
Area\n\nThere are several ways to find the area of a rhombus. The most common is (base × altitude).\n
Perimeter\n\nDistance around the rhombus. The sum of its side lengths. See Perimeter of a rhombus\n
Diagonals\n\nEach of the two diagonals is the perpendicular bisector of the other. See Diagonals of a rhombus

"/>
            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/textView4"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_alignParentLeft="true"
                android:layout_below="@+id/imageView1"
                android:layout_marginLeft="10dp"
                android:text="Formulas:"
                android:textSize="20sp"/>
            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/textView5"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_alignParentLeft="true"
                android:layout_below="@+id/imageView1"
                android:layout_marginLeft="10dp"
                android:text="Area of Rhombus: \n\n"
                android:textSize="20sp"/>
            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/textView9"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_alignParentLeft="true"
                android:layout_below="@+id/imageView1"
                android:layout_marginLeft="10dp"
                android:textColor="@color/purple"
                android:textStyle="bold"
                android:text=" 1/2*diagonal1*diagonal2 \n\n"
                android:textSize="20sp"/>

        </LinearLayout>
    </ScrollView>
</RelativeLayout>


